# Use hook or API rules to enforce batch update #5998
created: 2024-12-01, last updated: 2025-09-19, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/5998)

From my understanding of what you are trying to do, you could do it in a simpler way having a `group` field on every records of your collection.
...
const updatedRecord = await pb.collection("your_collection").getOne("record_id")
// Retrieve records ids from the same group
const records = await pb.collection("your_collection").getList(1, 50, {
filter: pb.filter("group = {:group1}", {group1: updatedRecord.group}),
fields: "id"
});
const updatedFields = { "field1": updatedRecord.field1, "field2": updatedRecord.field2 }
// Create a new batch instance
const batch = pb.createBatch()
// Register all update requests
for (let record of records) {
batch.collection("your_collection").update(record.id, updatedFields)
}
// Send the batch request
const result = await batch.send()
```
*Note: To achieve it with SDK you need to modify your API rules in order to allow others to view and update.
Otherwise, if you want to keep more restrictive API rules you can register a custom route where you send your update request and update all records that belong to the same group.*

